news.title: Noida-like township in Bundelkhand region could be a reality soon
news.para: While the idea is in its nascent stage, sources said the requisite initial budget required for the initiation of the ambitious project is likely to be drawn from the provisions for industrial development in the state budget 2023-2024.

news.title: Gujarat allocates Rs 1,066 crore to provide PMAY-Urban houses during next year
news.para: The government plans to spend Rs 1,066 crore on providing houses to around one lakh people under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (Urban) during the next year.

news.title: Land sale racket busted in Bhubaneswar
news.para: The EOW crackdown took place following a complaint lodged by Lipika Das of Khandagiri here on Tuesday. In her complaint, Das alleged that her 2,000 sqft vacant land at Malipada mouza in Khurda district was fraudulently sold to a man on October 21, 2020, without her knowledge.

news.title: Tamil Nadu housing board flats built in 2019 show cracks, peel off
news.para: At houses 105, 202, 211 and 212, in a tower used as a Covid-19 care centre, walls are damaged, doors broken, toilet pipes damaged and lifts defunct. Constant water seepage has left wet patches on walls.

news.title: MMRDA's two-day notice to family to vacate home irks Bombay HC
news.para: The action by Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority action had locked out the petitioner, S R Singh's family "from their only available residence.''

news.title: SVAMITVA Yojana: Drone survey of Uttar Pradesh villages to be completed by June
news.para: Recently chief minister Yogi Adityanath held a meeting with officials of the revenue department and directed the officials to complete the drone survey in the shortest time possible.

news.title: No STPs? Uttar Pradesh housing board asked to pay Rs 50,000 a day as fine
news.para: According to the UPPCB, the fine amount has been computed retrospectively to Rs 50,000 per day. For the past five years, the amount has been computed to about Rs 9 crore.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Waterbody & well destroyed to pave way for a housing project
news.para: T​​he Kukshet village residents were relocated in 1997, on grounds of growing pollution, to Nerul Sector 14. The MIDC, however, has given the plot to a private developer for a housing project. The developer has filled up the talav and the well.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh RERA directs CRDA to pay interest for flat allottees
news.para: The APRERA directed the APCRDA to pay the interest from June 30, 2022 till the time the flats are handed over to the allottees. The interest rate was decided as the Prime Lending Rate of State Bank of India + 2%.

news.title: Gurgram builder jumps from balcony to evade CBI arrest, fractures leg
news.para: A team of CBI had gone to his house to arrest with a warrant when Sanjiv Kumar, the accused, jumped from the balcony, said police.

news.title: Notices issued as per demarcation report of government: DDA
news.para: The DDA's submissions were made in an affidavit filed in response to a petition by a group of residents in Mehrauli, whose properties, along with various other properties, have been identified to be demolished as part of the 'anti-encroachment' drive.

news.title: One lakh housing units for poor in 2023-24 under PMAY: Haryana CM
news.para: Khattar said the government targeted to complete the allocation in the next financial year. For this purpose, the budget has allocated Rs 5,893 crore under project of housing for the poor.

news.title: Builder of affordable houses has to pay for upkeep of roads, parks: DTCP
news.para: This comes after homebuyers of affordable housing projects complained that developers are collecting upkeep fees ranging between Rs 2.50 and Rs 4 per sq ft from them in violation of the Affordable Housing Policy 2013.

news.title: In China, more families on the fence on home buying, foreclosures cloud sector
news.para: But more households were considering buying a home or investing in other assets in the coming three months, according to the survey by a research institute and think tank under Ant Group and the Southwestern University of Finance and Economics released on Wednesday.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh makes special allocation for metro rail projects in Agra, Kanpur in Budget 2023
news.para: ​"A budgetary provision of Rs 585 crore made for the Kanpur Metro Rail Project and provision of Rs 465 crore made for the Agra Metro Rail Project," a statement issued by the government said.
